Program: Great Lives
Title: Carl Gustav Jung
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00jxhdd
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 2 Jun 2017
Matthew Parris presents the biographical series in which his guests choose someone who has inspired their lives. Ruby Wax discusses the life and work of Carl Gustav Jung, who has been called 'the father of analytical psychology'. Along with author and Jungian analyst Professor Andrew Samuels, Ruby discusses Jung's theories of personality and psychological types, and reveals how his work has affected her own life. Show less